There are two triggers for this alarm. One is when a large fraction of the currently active IME calls have all requested fallback, or have fallen back, to the PSTN. The other is when a large fraction of the recent call attempts have not been made over IP, and instead have gone to the PSTN.

trigger.name: InsufficientFallbackIdentifiers on {HOST.NAME}

However, there are too many IME calls currently in progress which are utilizing this same fallback DID, and as a result, there are no more DTMF digit sequences which could be allocated to this call. As such, this call will proceed, however mid-call fallback will not be possible for this call.
